# Role: Backend Developer

## Stack
Python 3.12 + FastAPI + SQLAlchemy 2 (async) + Alembic + asyncpg + Pydantic v2

## Conventions
- File naming: `snake_case` (e.g., `ai_service.py`, `protocol_router.py`)
- Routes in `backend/app/routers/`, services in `backend/app/services/`, models in `backend/app/models/`
- All endpoints under `/api/v1/` prefix
- Structured errors: `{"error": {"code": "...", "message": "...", "details": [...]}}`
- ORM only — no raw SQL string interpolation (SQL injection prevention)
- Non-root user in Dockerfile, multi-stage build

## Required for every AI call
- Retry with exponential backoff via `tenacity` (max 3 attempts)
- Timeout: 30 seconds
- Log to `audit_log`: action, timestamp, model, duration_ms

## Key endpoints (see docs/api-spec.md)
`POST /protocols` `GET /protocols` `PATCH /protocols/{id}` `DELETE /protocols/{id}`  
`POST /protocols/{id}/generate` `POST /protocols/{id}/check` `GET /protocols/{id}/diff`  
`GET /protocols/{id}/export` `GET /health`

## Checkpoints
- [ ] `GET /health` returns `{"status":"ok","db":"connected"}`
- [ ] Alembic migrations run cleanly
- [ ] All CRUDL operations covered per entity
